#: /tmp/doc-l10n/cvs/press-release.HEAD/C/press_release.xml:16(title)
msgid "GNOME 2.12 Press Release"
msgstr "Datganiad i'r Wasg - GNOME 2.12"

#: /tmp/doc-l10n/cvs/press-release.HEAD/C/press_release.xml:20(title)
msgid "GNOME 2.12 DESKTOP AND DEVELOPER PLATFORM RELEASED"
msgstr "PLATFFORM PENBWRDD A DATBLYGWYR GNOME 2.12 WEDI EI RYDDHAU"

#: /tmp/doc-l10n/cvs/press-release.HEAD/C/press_release.xml:24(emphasis)
msgid "New version of the popular free-software desktop environment offers convenience and capability."
msgstr "Fersiwn newydd yr amgylchedd penbwrdd cod agored yn cynnig hwylustod a phŵer."

#: /tmp/doc-l10n/cvs/press-release.HEAD/C/press_release.xml:26(para)
msgid "BOSTON, Mass - September 7, 2005 - The GNOME Project today released the latest version of the GNOME Desktop and Developer Platform, the leading desktop for Linux and Unix operating systems. Version 2.12 improves the usability and power of GNOME in response to user feedback and developer contributions, and includes thousands of changes which refine the easiest and friendliest free software desktop."
msgstr "BOSTON, Massachusetts - Medi'r 7fed, 2005 - Heddiw, mi wnaeth Prosiect GNOME ryddhau eu fersiwn ddiweddaraf o Blatfform Penbwrdd a Datblygu GNOME, y penbwrdd mwyaf blaenllaw ar gyfer systemau rheoli Linux ac Unix. Mae fersiwn 2.12 yn gwella defnyddioldeb a phŵer GNOME mewn ymateb i adborth defnyddwyr a chyfraniadau datblygwyr, ac mae'n cynnwys miloedd o newidiadau sy'n coethi'r penbwrdd rhwyddaf a mwyaf cyfeillgar o fewn y byd cod agored."

#: /tmp/doc-l10n/cvs/press-release.HEAD/C/press_release.xml:28(para)
msgid "In keeping with GNOME's 'users first' philosophy, GNOME makes stable releases every six months. This allows developers and distributors to plan their GNOME-based products with confidence. As a result, distributions such as Fedora, SUSE, and Ubuntu will include GNOME 2.12 in the next release of their products, providing GNOME 2.12 to millions of users."
msgstr "Yn unol ag athroniaeth GNOME o gofio'r 'defnyddwyr yn gyntaf', mae GNOME yn creu fersiwn sefydlog newydd bob chwe mis. Mae hyn yn rhoi sicrwydd i ddatblygwyr a dosbarthwyr wrth iddyn nhw gynllunio eu cynnyrch sy'n seiliedig ar GNOME. Fel canlyniad, bydd dosbarthiadau megis Fedora, SuSE ac Ubuntu yn cynnwys GNOME 2.12 yn nosbarthiad nesaf eu cynnyrch, fydd yn darparu GNOME 2.12 i filiynau o ddefnyddwyr."

#: /tmp/doc-l10n/cvs/press-release.HEAD/C/press_release.xml:30(para)
msgid "Key features of GNOME 2.12 for users:"
msgstr "Prif nodweddion GNOME 2.12 i ddefnyddwyr:"

#: /tmp/doc-l10n/cvs/press-release.HEAD/C/press_release.xml:32(para)
msgid "An updated default theme."
msgstr "Thema ragosodedig wedi ei diweddaru."

#: /tmp/doc-l10n/cvs/press-release.HEAD/C/press_release.xml:33(para)
msgid "Easier file management."
msgstr "Yn haws i reoli ffeiliau."

#: /tmp/doc-l10n/cvs/press-release.HEAD/C/press_release.xml:34(para)
msgid "Intuitive clipboard behaviour."
msgstr "Y clipfwrdd yn gweithio mewn ffordd eglur."

#: /tmp/doc-l10n/cvs/press-release.HEAD/C/press_release.xml:35(para)
msgid "A unified document viewer."
msgstr "Gwyliwr dogfennau unedig."

#: /tmp/doc-l10n/cvs/press-release.HEAD/C/press_release.xml:36(para)
msgid "The About Me control panel."
msgstr "Y panel rheoli 'Amdanaf I':"

#: /tmp/doc-l10n/cvs/press-release.HEAD/C/press_release.xml:39(para)
msgid "System administrators will also welcome the new Services control panel, and menu editor. Software developers benefit from improvements to the underlying GTK+ toolkit, including integration of the next-generation cairo drawing toolkit from freedesktop.org."
msgstr "Bydd gweinyddwyr systemau hefyd yn croesawu'r panel rheoli Gwasanaethau newydd, a'r golygydd dewislenni. Bydd datblygwyr meddalwedd hefyd yn elwa o welliannau i'r gronfa feddalwedd GTK+, sy'n sail i GNOME. Mae'r gwelliannau yn cynnwys integreiddio'r gronfa lunio genhedlaeth-newydd, sef Cairo, o freedesktop.org."

#: /tmp/doc-l10n/cvs/press-release.HEAD/C/press_release.xml:41(para)
msgid "\"GNOME 2.12 looks better than ever before and brings greater consistency,\" said Owen Taylor, chairman of the GNOME Foundation's board. \"There are useful new features throughout the desktop, carefully implemented to increase usability while keeping GNOME simple and intuitive.\""
msgstr "\"Mae GNOME 2.12 yn edrych yn well nag erioed o'r blaen, ac mae'n cynnig mwy o gysondeb,\" medd Owen Taylor, cadeirydd bwrdd Sefydliad GNOME. \"Mae nodweddion newydd defnyddiol drwy gydol y penbwrdd, wedi'u gweithredu'n ofalus i gynyddu defnyddioldeb, tra'n cadw GNOME yn syml ac eglur i'w ddefnyddio.\""

#: /tmp/doc-l10n/cvs/press-release.HEAD/C/press_release.xml:43(para)
msgid "\"This release is the result of lots of hard work by a fantastic group of people,\" said Elijah Newren, GNOME's release manager. \"We are proud of our developers and proud of what they have produced.\""
msgstr "\"Mae'r fersiwn newydd hwn yn ganlyniad llawer o waith caled iawn gan garfan wych o bobl\", medd Elijah Newren, rheolwr rhyddhau GNOME. \"Rydym yn ymfalchïo yn ein datblygwyr ac yn ymfalchïo yn yr hyn maen nhw wedi ei greu.\""

#: /tmp/doc-l10n/cvs/press-release.HEAD/C/press_release.xml:45(para)
msgid "GNOME 2.12 is available in 43 languages, with many more languages partially supported. Galician, Estonian, Indonesian, Macedonian, Nepali, Slovak, Vietnamese, Thai, and Xhosa are new supported languages in GNOME 2.12."
msgstr "Mae GNOME 2.12 ar gael mewn 43 o ieithoedd (gan gynnwys y Gymraeg), gyda nifer fawr yn fwy o ieithoedd wedi'u cynnal yn rhannol. Mae Galisieg, Estoneg, Indoneseg, Macedoneg, Nepali, Slovak, Fietnameg, Thai, and Xhosa yn ieithoedd sydd wedi'u cynnal am y tro cyntaf yn GNOME 2.12."

#: /tmp/doc-l10n/cvs/press-release.HEAD/C/press_release.xml:47(title)
msgid "Availability"
msgstr "Ar gael"

#: /tmp/doc-l10n/cvs/press-release.HEAD/C/press_release.xml:48(para)
msgid "GNOME 2.12 will soon be available as part of most popular Linux distributions. For those who can't wait, the new GNOME LiveCD (available from <ulink url=\"http://www.gnome.org/start/2.12/\">www.gnome.org/start/2.12/</ulink>) allows users and journalists to test the latest GNOME desktop by burning a CD and rebooting - no installation is necessary."
msgstr "Bydd GNOME 2.12 ar gael yn fuan, o fewn y rhan fwyaf o ddosbarthiadau Linux poblogaidd. I'r rhai na all aros, mae'r CD byw GNOME newydd (ar gael oddi wrth <ulink url=\"http://www.gnome.org/start/2.12/\">www.gnome.org/start/2.12/</ulink>) yn gadael i ddefnyddwyr a newyddiadurwyr brofi'r penbwrdd GNOME diweddaraf drwy losgi CD ac ail-ddechrau'r cyfrifiadur - does ddim angen gosod unrhyw beth."

#: /tmp/doc-l10n/cvs/press-release.HEAD/C/press_release.xml:50(para)
msgid "Developers and advanced users wishing to install the GNOME 2.12 Desktop and Developer Platform now may download the software at <ulink url=\"http://ftp.gnome.org/pub/GNOME/desktop/\">http://ftp.gnome.org/pub/GNOME/desktop/</ulink> The software includes the source code for the GNOME 2.12 desktop interface and a complete set of developer tools and libraries."
msgstr "Gall datblygwyr a defnyddwyr blaengar sydd am osod Platfform Penbwrdd a Datblygu GNOME 2.12 wneud hynny nawr, a'i lwytho i lawr o <ulink url=\"http://ftp.gnome.org/pub/GNOME/desktop/\">http://ftp.gnome.org/pub/GNOME/desktop/</ulink>. Mae'r meddalwedd yn cynnwys yr holl ffynonellau craidd ar gyfer penbwrdd GNOME 2.12, a set gyflawn o arfau a llyfrgelloedd i ddatblygwyr."

#: /tmp/doc-l10n/cvs/press-release.HEAD/C/press_release.xml:53(title)
msgid "About GNOME"
msgstr "Ynghylch GNOME"

#: /tmp/doc-l10n/cvs/press-release.HEAD/C/press_release.xml:54(para)
msgid "GNOME is a free-software project developing a complete, easy to use desktop. Besides including central desktop components like system menus, a file manager, web browser, and utilities, GNOME is a complete development environment allowing developers to create new applications."
msgstr "Mae GNOME yn brosiect meddalwedd rhydd sy'n datblygu penbwrdd cyflawn, hawdd ei ddefnyddio. Yn ogystal â chynnwys elfennau craidd penbwrdd fel dewislenni system, trefnydd ffeiliau, porwr gwe, a gwasanaethau eraill, mae GNOME yn amgylchedd cyflawn i ddatblygwyr, sy'n gadael iddyn nhw greu rhaglenni newydd."

#: /tmp/doc-l10n/cvs/press-release.HEAD/C/press_release.xml:56(para)
msgid "More than 500 software developers from every continent, including more than 100 paid developers, contribute their time and effort to the project. Sponsors include industry leaders like Fluendo, HP, IBM, Novell, Red Hat, and Sun. GNOME is supported on a variety of platforms, including GNU/Linux (more commonly referred to as Linux), Solaris Operating Environment, HP-UX, Unix, BSD and Apple's Darwin."
msgstr "Mae dros 500 o ddatblygwyr meddalwedd o bob cyfandir, gan gynnwys dros 100 o rai sy'n cael eu talu i wneud hynny, yn cyfrannu eu hamser a'u hymdrechion at y prosiect. Caiff ei noddi gan rai o gwmnïoedd amlycaf y diwydiant, gan gynnwys Fluendo, HP, IBM, Novell, Red Hat, a Sun. Cynhelir GNOME ar amryw o blatfformau, gan gynnwys GNU/Linux (y cyfeirir ato'n fwy aml fel Linux), Amgylchedd Reoli Solaris, HP-UX, Unix, BSD, a Darwin oddi wrth Apple."

#: /tmp/doc-l10n/cvs/press-release.HEAD/C/press_release.xml:58(para)
msgid "The GNOME desktop is used by millions of people around the world. GNOME is a standard part of all leading Linux and Unix distributions worldwide, including those of popular community distributions like Debian, Fedora Core, and SUSE, and is the default desktop on major enterprise Linux distributions like Red Hat Enterprise Linux and Sun Java Desktop System. GNOME is also the desktop of choice for some of the world's biggest Linux desktop deployments, including large government deployments in Extremadura, Spain, and Sao Paulo, Brazil. GNOME's technology is used by major Linux ISVs such as Firefox, the Eclipse Project, Real Networks, and VMWare."
msgstr "Defnyddir penbwrdd GNOME gan filiynau o bobl ledled y byd. Mae GNOME yn rhan safonol o bob dosbarthiad blaenllaw o Linux ac Unix yn rhyngwladol, gan gynnwys dosbarthiadau cymunedol poblogaidd fel Debian, Fedora Core, a SuSE. GNOME hefyd yw'r penbwrdd rhagosodedig ar ddosbarthiadau Linux blaenllaw ar gyfer corfforaethau, fel Red Hat Enterprise Linux a'r Java Desktop System oddi wrth Sun. GNOME hefyd yw'r penbwrdd ddewiswyd ar rai o osodiadau Linux mwyaf y byd, gan gynnwys gosodiadau mawr gan lywodraethau yn Extremadura, Sbaen, ac yn Sao Paulo, Brasil. Defnyddir technoleg GNOME gan werthwyr mawr o feddalwedd annibynnol i Linux, fel Firefox, prosiect Eclipse, Real Networks, a VMWare."

#: /tmp/doc-l10n/cvs/press-release.HEAD/C/press_release.xml:60(para)
msgid "More information on GNOME can be found at <ulink url=\"http://www.gnome.org\">http://www.gnome.org/</ulink>"
msgstr "Ceir mwy o wybodaeth am GNOME ar <ulink url=\"http://www.gnome.org\">http://www.gnome.org/</ulink>"

#: /tmp/doc-l10n/cvs/press-release.HEAD/C/press_release.xml:63(title)
msgid "About the GNOME Foundation"
msgstr "Ynghylch Sefydliad GNOME"

#: /tmp/doc-l10n/cvs/press-release.HEAD/C/press_release.xml:64(para)
msgid "Comprised of hundreds of volunteer developers and industry-leading companies, the GNOME Foundation is an organization committed to supporting the advancement of GNOME. The Foundation is a member directed, non-profit organization that provides financial, organizational and legal support to the GNOME project and helps determine its vision and roadmap. More information on the GNOME Foundation can be found at <ulink url=\"http://foundation.gnome.org/\">foundation.gnome.org</ulink>."
msgstr "Yn cynnwys cannoedd o ddatblygwyr gwirfoddol a chwmnïoedd sydd amlycaf o fewn eu diwydiannau, cymdeithas yw Sefydliad GNOME sydd wedi ymrwymo i hybu ac i symud GNOME ymlaen. Mae'r Sefydliad yn cael ei arwain gan ei aelodau, ac mae'n fudiad dielw sy'n cynnig cymorth ariannol, cyfundrefnol a chyfreithiol i brosiect GNOME, ac yn helpu pennu ei weledigaeth a'i strategaeth. Ceir mwy o wybodaeth ynglŷn â Sefydliad GNOME ar <ulink url=\"http://foundation.gnome.org/\">foundation.gnome.org</ulink>."

#: /tmp/doc-l10n/cvs/press-release.HEAD/C/press_release.xml:67(title)
msgid "Press Inquiries"
msgstr "Ymholiadau'r Wasg"

#: /tmp/doc-l10n/cvs/press-release.HEAD/C/press_release.xml:68(para)
msgid "Please direct press inquiries to <ulink url=\"mailto:gnome-press-contact@gnome.org\">gnome-press-contact@gnome.org</ulink>."
msgstr "Gyrrwch ymholiadau'r wasg at <ulink url=\"mailto:gnome-press-contact@gnome.org\">gnome-press-contact@gnome.org</ulink>, os gwelwch yn dda."

#: /tmp/doc-l10n/cvs/press-release.HEAD/C/press_release.xml:70(emphasis)
msgid "Linux is a trademark of Linus Torvalds. All other names and trademarks are the property of their respective owners."
msgstr "Mae Linux yn nod masnach sy'n eiddo i Linus Torvalds. Mae pob enw a nod masnach arall yn eiddo i'w berchnogion perthnasol."

